<item>
            <title>[BEAM-12422] Vendored gRPC 1.36.0 is using a log4j version with security issues</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-12422</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Automatic security scanners report this vulnerability&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2017-5645&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2017-5645&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is defined during vendoring here &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/3c9807bfb4e00a8f8564b4688e01ad5c8c2189d2/buildSrc/src/main/groovy/org/apache/beam/gradle/GrpcVendoring_1_36_0.groovy#L71&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/3c9807bfb4e00a8f8564b4688e01ad5c8c2189d2/buildSrc/src/main/groovy/org/apache/beam/gradle/GrpcVendoring_1_36_0.groovy#L71&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
