                            <comment id="17353338" author="iemejia" created="Fri, 28 May 2021 13:10:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=suztomo&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;suztomo&quot;&gt;suztomo&lt;/a&gt; do you know why we are defining log4j explicitly there? I wonder if we really need this dependency. Seems to come from a transitive dependency no? I suppose gRPC does not use log4j directly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17355095" author="suztomo" created="Tue, 1 Jun 2021 13:28:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think you&apos;re right. gRPC uses &lt;tt&gt;java.util.logging.Logger&lt;/tt&gt;. Log4J does not seem necessary here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17372975" author="lcwik" created="Thu, 1 Jul 2021 17:56:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;netty uses log4j and commons-logging and is a transitive dep of grpc.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
